    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4072763090" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4072763090" />
    <a title="Marieke" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/71842240-marieke"><img alt="Marieke" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612125302p2/71842240.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4072763090?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marieke" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marieke" href="/user/show/71842240-marieke">Marieke</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/21954434-wind-sand-and-stars">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71842240-marieke?shelf=european-lit">european-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71842240-marieke?shelf=french-lit">french-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4072763090" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9835740115969313840">Never would I have expected to fall in love with a book about airplanes and flying. The intricate way Antoine de Saint-Exupéry has woven in all sorts of philosophical ponderings and life lessons in his stories came as a very pleasant surprise, I underlined so many quotes in this little book. Many of his adventures will stay with me for a long time: almost dying of thirst in a desert, surviving plane crashes, setting free a slave to return to his home town and experiencing the Spanish civil war- </span>
  <span id="freeText9835740115969313840" style="display:none">Never would I have expected to fall in love with a book about airplanes and flying. The intricate way Antoine de Saint-Exupéry has woven in all sorts of philosophical ponderings and life lessons in his stories came as a very pleasant surprise, I underlined so many quotes in this little book. Many of his adventures will stay with me for a long time: almost dying of thirst in a desert, surviving plane crashes, setting free a slave to return to his home town and experiencing the Spanish civil war- I can't believe this man has gone through all of that. I can certainly see how he came to write Le Petit Prince after all of his adventures in the air and the Sahara desert, and I think I love that book even more for it now. <br /><br />Honestly, I would recommend this book to anyone, whether you've read Antoine de Saint-Exupéry before or not. Some of the airplane technical text went over my head, but I didn't need it to be able to fully place myself into that plane he was flying, through storm, guided by the stars, over deserts and mountains. In a time where travelling still isn't the safest thing to do, this book fulfilled a bit of my wanderlust. Just wonderful.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9835740115969313840" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

